    <div class="highlight-box">
      <h2>Renewable Energy Explained</h2>
      <p>Renewable energy is power that is gathered from natural phenomena, like tidal motion or the sun. Renewables typically do not involve the removal of resources from the environment, or infrastructure that has a permanent effect on the environment. Examples include wind, solar, geothermal, and hydroelectric power.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="side-by-side">
      <figure>
        <img src="images/Shungnak-Solar_Blue-Planet-Energy1000x750.jpeg" alt="SolarPanels">
        <figcaption>Solar array in Shungnak, Alaska</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="text-box-right">
        <h3>Solar Energy</h3>
        <p>Solar energy works by capturing photons from sunlight and turning them into electrons. This solar array in Shungnak, Alaska is designed to optimize energy capture during long daylight hours.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="side-by-side">
      <figure>
        <img src="images/Aerial_View_of_Salmon_Arch_dam_in_Juneau-830x615.jpeg" alt="SalmonCreekDam">
        <figcaption>Salmon Creek Dam, Juneau</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="text-box-left">
        <h3>Hydroelectric</h3>
        <p>Hydroelectric power uses the force of water to spin turbines that generate an electric current. Salmon Creek Dam represents early 20th-century innovation in hydroelectric energy. Today, it remains a key part of Juneau’s renewable energy supply.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="side-by-side">
      <figure>
        <img src="images/Screenshot 2025-06-08 at 21.55.20.png" alt="WindTurbine">
        <figcaption>Fire Island Wind Farm, Alaska</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="text-box-right">
        <h3>Wind Power</h3>
        <p>Windmills have been in use for centuries to power grain mills. Modern wind technology employs turbines that capture the kinetic energy of air currents with spinning blades to generate electricity. In Southcentral Alaska, on Fire Island or Natul’iv in Dena’ina Athabascan, an 11 turbine system provides energy for over 7000 homes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

